pr_body:
This PR modifies one existing function: - ``pgr_withPointsKSP``: - Improving the 'driver_side' optional parameter to compulsory parameter. - Adding two new result columns 'start_vid' and 'end_vid'. - Normalizing the output. This is a final merge PR containing commits from several different PRs combined. The intermediate PRs made on the [GSoC-pgRouting](https://github.com/pgRouting/GSoC-pgRouting/) repository are as follows: | Description | Pull Requests | | -----------| --------------------- | | pgr_withPointsKSP |
  • pgRouting/GSoC-pgRouting#292
  • pgRouting/GSoC-pgRouting#297
  • pgRouting/GSoC-pgRouting#306
  • pgRouting/GSoC-pgRouting#308
  • pgRouting/GSoC-pgRouting#314

| The wiki page with more details on this project can be found [here](https://github.com/pgRouting/pgrouting/wiki/GSoC-2023-Implement-pgr_withPointsKSP-and-Add-Overloads).
